events.title: ff MASSIVE 2014 PARTY ONE (FREE W/ RSVP ON DO512)
events.description:
"ff MASSIVE is back at SXSW Interactive! This year, ff Venture Capitaland their portfolio companies will be taking over Empire Control Room and Garage (7th and Red River) for a weekend of fun, games, food, drinks and merriment.


Stop by the Empire Garage on Saturday March 8 and Sunday March 9 from 1pm to 5pm to hang out, network, and meet the founders and senior teams of ffVC’s startups. Enterprise-focused companies will be highlighted on Saturday, and Consumer-facing startups will be featured on Sunday. Both afternoons will also contain topic-specific discourse and discussions, snacks, beverages, and plenty of entertainment.


For example, ffVC portfolio company Distil is bringing life-sized Rock ‘Em Sock ‘Em Robots. anyone can fight with their friends, or watch venture capitalists and tech journalists fight each other.


For those who want something a bit more relaxing, InteraXon, also a ffVC portfolio company, is unveiling the Muse Chill Challenge, so ff MASSIVE guests can see what it takes to calm their minds, with a little help from the Muse headband.


ff MASSIVE will continue into the PM with live music, DJs, and cocktails, kicking off each night at 9 pm. Friday features Robert Delong and The Octopus Project. Saturday will be all about rock ‘n’ roll, with Vintage Trouble, local Austin rockers The Eastern Sea and Walker Lukens and the Side Arms. Sundaynight will turn into an epic DJ dance party with IHEARTCOMIX, featuring sets from Jay-Z producer Just Blaze as well as AraabMuzik + many many more.


For more info visit ffmassive.com"

events.description:
Listen to Black Out Days
Phantogram is an American electronic rock duo from Saratoga Springs, New York, formed in 2007 and consisting of Sarah Barthel and Josh Carter. They write and record in a remote barn in upstate New York called Harmony Lodge. The band name was partially inspired by an optical illusion called a phantogram, in which two-dimensional images appear to be three-dimensional. They described their sound as "street beat, psych pop". According to Josh Carter, their music has "lots of rhythms, swirling guitars, spacey keyboards, echoes, airy vocals". The band released a studio album (Eyelid Movies in 2009), four EPs (Phantogram and Running From the Cops in 2009, Nightlife in 2011, Phantogram in 2013) and five singles.
